{
    "id": "composting/start",
    "title": "Start a Compost Bucket",
    "description": "Build a compost bucket using hydroponic plant leftovers and kitchen-style browns.",
    "image": "/assets/quests/compost_start_bucket.jpg",
    "npc": "/assets/npc/nova.jpg",
    "start": "start",
    "dialogue": [
        {
            "id": "start",
            "text": "Waste not, friend! We'll turn your hydroponic leftovers into compost. I'll show you exactly where to run the process so you don't get stuck.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "where-to-run",
                    "text": "Perfect—where do I do this?"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-1",
                    "text": "I know the basics—quiz me first"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "where-to-run",
            "text": "Open Inventory, find your **5 gallon bucket**, then open that item's page. Processes live on item pages in the Process section. Look for **Start a Compost Bucket** and check its required inputs and output item before you click run.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "inputs",
                    "text": "Got it: inventory item page → process section"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "inputs",
            "text": "For this run you'll need: a bucket, gloves, plus organic matter. Use hydroponic leftovers like a **harvested basil plant** and **bundle of basil leaves** as your green feedstock.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "basics",
                    "text": "Teach me the compost basics before I run it"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-1",
                    "text": "Quiz me now"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "basics",
            "text": "Fast rules: aim for roughly 2:1 browns to greens, moisture like a wrung sponge, and regular aeration. Avoid meat, dairy, oily food, and pet waste in this small bucket system.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-1",
                    "text": "Let's do the quiz"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "build",
                    "text": "Skip quiz and build now"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-1",
            "text": "Quiz 1: Which materials count as compost greens?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-2",
                    "text": "Fresh plant scraps and coffee grounds"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-greens",
                    "text": "Dry cardboard and sawdust"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-greens",
                    "text": "Plastic wrappers"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "retry-greens",
            "text": "Close! Greens are nitrogen-rich wet organics like fresh trimmings. Dry paper and leaves are browns.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-1",
                    "text": "Retry quiz"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-2",
            "text": "Quiz 2: What's the target moisture level?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-3",
                    "text": "Damp like a wrung-out sponge"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-moisture",
                    "text": "Bone dry so mold cannot grow"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-moisture",
                    "text": "Soaked and dripping"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "retry-moisture",
            "text": "Not quite. Too dry slows microbes; too wet causes odor and compaction.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-2",
                    "text": "Retry quiz"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-3",
            "text": "Quiz 3: Why do we turn or fluff a compost bucket?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-4",
                    "text": "To add oxygen and keep decomposition aerobic"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-aeration",
                    "text": "To remove all microbes"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-aeration",
                    "text": "To cool it to freezer temperatures"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "retry-aeration",
            "text": "Yep, aeration is for oxygen and even decomposition. Anaerobic pockets are what create foul smells.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-3",
                    "text": "Retry quiz"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-4",
            "text": "Quiz 4: Which input should you avoid in this bucket compost?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-5",
                    "text": "Meat and dairy scraps"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-avoid",
                    "text": "Shredded paper"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-avoid",
                    "text": "Dry leaves"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "retry-avoid",
            "text": "Correct materials to avoid include meat, dairy, oily foods, and pet waste because they attract pests and smell.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-4",
                    "text": "Retry quiz"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-5",
            "text": "Quiz 5: What active compost temperature range usually indicates strong microbial activity?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "build",
                    "text": "About 50–65 °C (122–149 °F)"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-temp",
                    "text": "0–10 °C (32–50 °F)"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-temp",
                    "text": "90–100 °C (194–212 °F)"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "retry-temp",
            "text": "Hot compost is warm, not boiling. Around 50–65 °C helps decomposition and suppresses many weed seeds.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-5",
                    "text": "Retry quiz"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "build",
            "text": "Great. Back to execution: go to the 5 gallon bucket item page, open its Process section, verify required inputs, and run **Start a Compost Bucket**. If the output says layered compost bucket, you're done right.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "process",
                    "process": "start-compost-bin",
                    "goto": "build",
                    "text": "Run Start a Compost Bucket on the item page"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "finish",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "025862b3-8377-4396-ab32-aa572bdc3260",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ],
                    "text": "Process ran and I got the layered compost bucket"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "finish",
            "text": "Excellent work. You set up airflow, fed real organic matter, and confirmed the output correctly. Keep adding greens under a brown cap and turn it regularly.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "finish",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "025862b3-8377-4396-ab32-aa572bdc3260",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ],
                    "text": "Compost bucket started"
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
